<title type="html"><![CDATA[Zelda 2 &quot;Microchip&quot; shortage was a hoax?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=633&amp;p=5244#p5244"><![CDATA[
Does anyone remember the reason big N said that Zelda 2 was delayed due to a microchip shortage?<br /><br />We all know that Zelda 2 is a MMC1, (SKROM to be exact), which used a 128KB PRG ROM and 128KB CHR ROM.<br /><br />MMC1 was pretty common, in most every game at the time. The 128KB mask roms and the CIC were probably also very common, so I don't see any reason this could be delayed due to a chip shortage.<br /><br />Maybe Punch-Out which was the only one that used a "MMC2/4" could be delayed to to a shortage.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=45">drk421</a> — Fri Oct 07, 2005 6:14 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
